-- Arsenal Humbles Manchester City 3-0, Moves Into Second in Premier League
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2010-10-24T16:55:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-24/arsenal-beats-10-man-manchester-city-3-0-to-go-second-in-premier-league.html
Arsenal beat 10-man Manchester City
3-0 to climb into second spot in English soccer’s Premier
League, ahead of today’s opponent and Manchester United on goal
difference.  Samir Nasri, Alex Song and Nicklas Bendtner scored for the
Gunners at Eastlands to end a run of four straight league
victories for City, which had center-back Dedryck Boyata red-
carded after only five minutes today.  Arsenal, Manchester United and City all trail defending
champion Chelsea by five points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  